com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.device.connection

Class WiBeatConnection

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.device.connection.WiBeatConnection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseDeviceConnection

    public class WiBeatConnection
extends Object
implements BaseDeviceConnection
    Allows to establish connection with WiBeat device. Used for reading and writing device GATT characteristics.

    All read and write operations are added in the queue, so no need to wait for finishing the previous operation.

    Note: Application should call disconnect() as early as possible after executing job with the device.
    Usage: 

     WiBeatConnection connection;
 ...
 connection=new WiBeatConnection(context, "AA:AA:AA:AA:AA:AA", new WiBeatConnection.WiBeatConnectionListener() {
 
    
  @Override
  public void onConnect() {
      //Interact with beacon
      //Read advertising interval
      connection.readAdvertisingInterval(new WiBeatConnection.WiBeatReadListener() {
 
    
          @Override
          public void onSuccess(WiBeatCharacteristic powerMoteCharacteristic) {
              if (powerMoteCharacteristic.getType() == WiBeatCharacteristicType.ADVERTISING_INTERVAL) {
                  int interval = powerMoteCharacteristic.getIntValue();
              }
          }
 
    
          @Override
          public void onError(WiBeatError powerMoteError, WiBeatCharacteristicType powerMoteCharacteristicType) {
              //Handle error
          }
      });
  }
 
    
  @Override
  public void onDisconnect() {
      ...
  }
 
    
  @Override
  public void onError(WiBeatError powerMoteError) {
      //Handle error
  }
 });
 connection.connect();

      • writeCalibratedTxPowerLevels

        public void writeCalibratedTxPowerLevels(byte[] txPowerLevels,
                                         WiBeatConnection.WiBeatWriteListener writeListener)
                                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Write calibrated TX power levels array. The Power levels array must contain a 8 values from the next range: [-90, -1] dBm.

        This is an asynchronous operation. Once the write operation has been completed successfully, the onSuccess callback is invoked, otherwise onError callback is triggered.

        Parameters:
        txPowerLevels - New TX power levels
        writeListener - Write listener
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - then the txPowerLevels is null or not contain 4 values
        Since:
        1.2.0
        See Also:
        WiBeatWriteListener
